title: subarashii_pose
body:
Stock mad scientist pose in Japanese media. Both palms open and turned skyward, with [[outstretched arms|arms outstretched]] and raised slightly in a confident, 'welcoming' gesture. Arms may sometimes be raised higher above the head. Legs usually remain standing, spread apart slightly (though some may have them close together as if standing at attention).

Often accompanied with the stock exclamation of "SUBARASHII", hence the name. This is usually translated into English as "magnificent" [tn](c.f. [[Bondrewd]])[/tn], "majestic" [tn](c.f. [[micolash_host_of_the_nightmare|Micolash]])[/tn], "marvelous"  [tn](also [[Bondrewd]])[/tn], "wonderful", "magnifique", etc.

Mad scientists in Western works may also sometimes strike a similar pose, but this is far less common, as they tend to prefer other more intimidating poses.

The standard Western equivalent generally involves one arm raised and clenched in a claw-like pose, with the other raised higher and 'pointed' towards the general direction of the viewer or another character. This second arm can be either 'open' or clenched closed, and is usually also holding another object: generally a test tube, flask, ray gun, wrench, or some other 'sciencey' implement.

title: tattoo_sleeve
body: A sleeve tattoo or tattoo sleeve is a large [[tattoo]] or collection of smaller, usually connected tattoos that covers most or all of a person's arm or leg. While a 'full' sleeve will cover the entire arm from shoulder to wrist or entire leg from groin to ankle, there are also 'half' and 'quarter' sleeves which cover less, but will still typically envelop the entire arm just as a garment would.

title: gorosei
body:
The [b]Gorosei[/b], or the [b]Five Elders[/b], are the group of five elite [[Celestial Dragons (one piece)|]] who co-ruled the World Government. As such, they served as the overarching main antagonists of the [[One Piece]] series.

Each member posses an extremely powerful Mythical [[Devil Fruit]] that allows them to transform into a gigantic monsters. In addition, they are practically immortal, as they are capable of regenerating even when their body were shattered to pieces.

[spoiler]In reality, they are serving under the secretive supreme ruler of the World Government [[Imu (one piece)|]], who granted them immortality. They acts as the "public" face of their authority.[/spoiler]

title: boa_hancock
body:
[[One Piece]] character. She is the captain of the Kuja Pirates and the current empress of Amazon Lily. Also known as the "Snake Princess" and "Pirate Empress" due to her beauty, and one of the [[Shichibukai]].

She has two younger sisters, [[Boa Sandersonia|Sandersonia]] and [[Boa Marigold|Marigold]], and is often seen alongside her pet snake [[Salome (one piece)|]]. She would later on developed a crush on [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]] during the Amazon Lily Arc.

Having consumed the Mero Mero no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], she can fire heart beams, bullets and arrows that turn anyone who is caught by her charm into stone.

[spoiler]Hancock along with her sisters were kidnapped and sold as slaves to a member of the [[Celestial Dragons (one piece)|]] during their childhood. Because of this, she suffered much abuse while enslaved and developed a hatred for males. Hancock's hatred later softened after she developed a crush on Luffy, who was the first man who acknowledged her suffering.[/spoiler]

title: senran_kagura_new_link
body:
[b]Shinobi Master: Senran Kagura NEW LINK[/b] ([b]シノビマスター 閃乱カグラ NEW LINK[/b]), officially abbreviated as  [b]ShinoMas[/b] ([b]シノマス[/b]), is a free-to-play collectible [[card_(medium)|card]] RPG for mobile devices. It was released to Android and iOS on November 29, 2017.

The game features each of the four schools from the [[senran kagura shinovi versus|Versus]] games, with more characters being added through periodic updates. Like [[Senran Kagura New Wave]], the gameplay centers around collecting cards, but in addition to the illustrations, each card unlocks a costume for use in [[3D]] turn-based combat.

It will end its live services on May 30, 2025, but an "offline" version will still be available after that date.

title: quattro_bajeena
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] series, [b]Quattro Bajeena[/b] is a male character and supporting protagonist in Mobile Suit [[Zeta Gundam]]. An [[AEUG]] veteran [[mobile_suit|MS]] [[pilot]], Captain Quattro pilots a red [[Rick Dias]], the [[Gundam Mk II]] and the [[Hyaku Shiki]]. He also pilots the [[zero_shiki_(gundam)|Zero Shiki]] and the [[Delta Gundam]] as simulator data.

The official [[Bandai]] romanization of his name is "Quattro Bajeena", and also (humorously) "Quattro Vagina" in several PS1 Gundam games, such as SD Gundam G-Generation F and Char's Counterattack.

In an infamous letter in [[Engrish text|Engrish]] to [[Hayato Kobayashi]] (post #14851), [[Kai Shiden]] writes:

[spoiler][i]"Captain Quattro, he is a CHAR"[/i]: Quattro Bajeena is the pseudonym [[Char Aznable]] uses throughout [[Zeta Gundam]].[/spoilers] 

[spoilers]Quattro/Char's Hyaku Shiki MS was severely damaged in battle during his final duel with [[Haman Karn]] (in her [[Qubeley]]). Apparently destroyed after Haman defeats Quattro, its wreckage is later shown floating in space with its [[cockpit]] hatch open, implying Quattro/Char's survival of the encounter.[/spoilers]

title: nintendo_switch
body:
[[Nintendo|Nintendo's]] seventh game console, released in the Eighth Generation of consoles and the successor to the [[Wii U]]. Known as the NX during development. The first production model went on sale on March 3rd, 2017. 

The Nintendo Switch has two dedicated [[game controller]]s (one for each hand) called [[Joy-Con]]s. These can be attached to and removed from the console at will, essentially making it a hybrid home/handheld platform.

A smaller version, the [[nintendo switch lite|Switch Lite]], was revealed July 10th, 2019, built strictly for handheld gaming. The Lite has no detachable Joy-Cons; the controllers are hard-built into the console. It also has no HDMI output so cannot be connected to a TV like the original model Switch can. A [[nintendo switch - oled model|higher-end version]] featuring an OLED screen was released on October 8, 2021. 

The platform has enjoyed a positive reception and high sales numbers in the years since its release. In addition to carrying many popular flagship titles like [[The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild]] and [[Super Mario Odyssey]], the Switch has also become a welcoming home for many older games from last-gen systems. This led the Switch to be the [i]de facto[/i] portable way to play popular older titles like [[Diablo 3]], [[Dark Souls I]] and [[Castle Crashers]] which had previously only been playable on non-portable platforms. As of early 2023, the combined Switch product line is one of the best-selling platforms in Nintendo's entire history, outselling both the [[Wii]] and the [[Game Boy]] and now second only to the [[Nintendo DS]].

For tagging purposes, if the Switch has its Joy-Cons detached (or is being controlled by other compatible controllers), tag it as a [[game console]] (post #3259420, post #3528468). If the Switch has at least one Joy-Con connected or the console itself is the Lite, tag it as a [[handheld game console]] (post #3471232, post #3470179).

title: song_of_the_south
body:
Controversial 1946 [[Disney]] animated and live-action movie about a young boy Johnny and his friendship with the [[Uncle Remus]]. As the movie is set a plantation in the Reconstruction era after the [[American Civil War]], the film featured a large number of [[racism|racist]] black stereotypes, which led to the movie being a subject of polarizing debate and was withheld from re-release by Disney ever since.

Aside from racial stereotype issue, it is more positively well known for it's animated segments featuring talking animals which are still used in [[Disneyland]] and related merch.

title: paresthesia
body:
An abnormal sensation of the skin (tingling, pricking, chilling, burning, numbness) with no apparent physical cause. It happens when sustained pressure is placed on a nerve (from [[seiza|sitting with legs crossed for too long]], or [[arm_pillow|fallen asleep with an arm crooked under their head]]...) . The feeling quickly goes away once the pressure is relieved.

Also known in English as "[body part] falling asleep" or "[[pin]]s and [[needle]]s".

title: mazda_furai
body: The Mazda Furai was a concept car revealed on 27 December 2007. It had Mazda's flagship rotary engine design and chassis based on real Le-Mans car. The car wore the number 55, that of its 1991 24 Hours of Le Mans-winning ancestor, the [[Mazda 787B|787B]]. While the [[Top Gear]] test driver Mark Ticehurst was piloting the Furai on August 19, 2008, it suddenly caught fire, ultimately burning down almost completely, while the pilot escaped fire unscathed. Mazda then abandoned the project, and no news followed.

Distortion is a recurring phenomena in [[Project Moon]] media, first introduced in [[Library Of Ruina]] before being expanded upon in [[The Distortion Detective]] and [[Limbus Company]].

Distortion is primarily caused when an individual communicates with the Voice ([spoiler][[Carmen (project moon)|]][/spoiler]) and accepts their offer rather than reject them, or by being in proximity of a Monolith.

Distortion causes an individual to change into a distorted/monstrous version of themselves, which is usually permanent (and can eventually result in the individual transforming into an Abnormality), but can be reversed. One may even manifest [[E.G.O (project moon)|]] after distorting, or vice versa.

title: kastus_kalinouski_regiment
body:
The [b]Kastus Kalinouski Regiment[/b] is a Belarusian volunteer military unit fighting under Ukrainian command in the [[Russo-Ukrainian War]]. Originally formed in 2022 as the Kastus Kalinouski Battalion, it was later expanded into a regiment due to an influx of volunteers. Named after [[Kastus Kalinouski]], a 19th-century Belarusian revolutionary, the unit consists of Belarusians opposing the pro-Russian regime of [[Alexander Lukashenko]] and supporting Ukraine against Russian aggression.

The regiment operates as part of [[Ukrainian_Ground_Forces|Ukraine’s Armed Forces]] and has participated in multiple engagements against Russian forces. While it is primarily a military unit, it also represents a broader anti-Lukashenko resistance movement, advocating for a democratic Belarus free from Russian influence.

Since its formation, the Kastus Kalinouski Regiment has been a target of Russian and Belarusian state propaganda, which portrays it as a terrorist organization and an instrument of Western influence. Despite this, the regiment remains a key symbol of Belarusian opposition to authoritarian rule and continues to attract volunteers.

title: international_legion_of_ukraine
body:
The [b]International Legion of Ukraine[/b] is a foreign volunteer military unit operating under the [[Ukrainian_ground_forces|Armed Forces of Ukraine]]. Established in February 2022, it was created in response to Ukraine's call for foreign fighters to help defend the country against [[russo-ukrainian_war|Russia’s full-scale invasion]]. The unit consists of volunteers from multiple nations, including the United States, the United Kingdom, Canada, Poland, Georgia, and others.

The legion is structured similarly to Ukraine’s military and is divided into battalions based on nationality and language. It has been involved in frontline combat, reconnaissance, and special operations across various battle zones, including Kyiv, Kharkiv, and Donetsk.

Since its formation, the unit has been a subject of Russian disinformation, with Kremlin sources branding its members as "mercenaries" and threatening them with execution if captured. Despite these claims, the Ukrainian government recognises the legion as an official part of its armed forces, ensuring that its members are treated as lawful combatants under the Geneva Conventions.

title: kraken_regiment
body:
The [b]Kraken Regiment[/b] is a Ukrainian special forces unit operating under the [[directorate_of_intelligence_(ukraine)|Defence Intelligence of Ukraine]] (GUR). Formed in February 2022 at the onset of the [[Russo-Ukrainian war|Russian full-scale invasion of Ukraine]], it was established by veterans of the [[azov_battalion|Azov Regiment]] and other military volunteers. Unlike Azov, it is not part of the [[national_guard_of_ukraine|National Guard]] but operates under Ukraine’s military intelligence, giving it a degree of operational independence.

Based in [[Kharkiv]], the Kraken Regiment has participated in several high-profile operations, including urban warfare, reconnaissance, and sabotage missions against Russian forces. It is known for its aggressive tactics and unconventional warfare, often conducting deep-strike raids behind enemy lines.

Due to its ties to Azov, Russian propaganda frequently portrays the Kraken Regiment as an extremist group, though the unit itself does not officially use far-right symbols or rhetoric. It remains one of Ukraine’s most elite and secretive special forces units, playing a crucial role in defending and liberating occupied territories.

title: 3rd_assault_brigade
body:
The [b]3rd Separate Assault Brigade[/b] is a dynamic unit within [[Ukrainian_ground_forces|Ukraine's Ground Forces]], comprising approximately 900 soldiers. Originally established as a volunteer force in the early stages of the [[Russo-Ukrainian War|]], it was founded on February 24, 2022, under the leadership of "Andriy Biletsky":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andriy_Biletsky], a figure known for his role in creating the [[azov_battalion|Azov Regiment]]. Initially rooted in the Azov Special Operations Forces (SSO) and [[Territorial_Defence_Forces_(Ukraine)|Territorial Defense]] volunteers, the brigade was officially integrated into the Ukrainian military structure in January 2023. It has since played a pivotal role in intense combat operations, including the defense of Bakhmut and the liberation of areas like Kherson and Andriivka.


Much like its predecessor, the Azov Regiment, the 3rd Assault Brigade has faced scrutiny for its historical ties to far-right ideologies and the use of symbols such as the [[Wolfsangel]] in its early days, sparking controversy over alleged neo-Nazi associations. Critics point to its origins within the broader Azov movement, while supporters argue it has evolved into a professional fighting force, distancing itself from extremist roots as it merged with the Ground Forces. Russian propaganda continues to amplify these criticisms, portraying the brigade as a symbol of extremism to justify its actions in the conflict. Today, the brigade's insignia features a stylized "Idea of the Nation" symbol—three golden slashes—reflecting a shift toward Ukrainian national identity over past controversial emblems.

body:
The [b]Azov Regiment[/b] is a 900 men unit of Ukraine's national gendarmerie ([[National Guard of Ukraine]]). First based in Mariupol and initially formed as a volunteer militia during the [[Russo-Ukrainian war]], it has participated in eight engagements. The unit was founded in May 2014 as a volunteer paramilitary militia under the command of "Andriy Biletsky":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andriy_Biletsky] to fight pro-Russian forces in the Donbas War, and was formally incorporated into the National Guard on 11 November 2014.

The group has drawn controversy over its early and allegedly continuing association with far-right groups and neo-[[Nazi]] ideology, its early use of controversial symbols linked to Nazism (the [[black sun (symbol)|]], the [[Wolfsangel]] and the [[swastika]]), and allegations that members of the group have participated in torture and war crimes.  However, some experts argue that the regiment has evolved beyond its origins as street militia, tempering its neo-Nazi underpinnings as it became part of the Ukranian National Guard. 

Since 2014, criticism of the Azov Regiment has been a recurring theme of Russian politics and more recently as [[Vladimir Putin]]'s justification for invading Ukraine, the prominence of the unit in Ukraine's military forces being expanded and exaggerated by Russian media to this day.

The most recent official Azov Regiment logo now only uses a heavily altered Wolfsangel symbol, while the SSO (special forces) units don't use it at all (they use a [[tryzub]] formed out of swords instead).

title: freedom_of_russia_legion
body:
The [b]Freedom of Russia Legion[/b] is a military unit composed of Russian defectors, volunteers, and anti-Kremlin fighters operating under the [[ukrainian_ground_forces|Armed Forces of Ukraine]]. It was formed in March 2022, following [[russo-ukrainian_war|Russia’s full-scale invasion of Ukraine]], and consists of Russian citizens who oppose [[Vladimir Putin]]’s government and seek to overthrow it.

The legion has participated in combat operations against Russian forces, primarily in Eastern Ukraine. In addition to fighting on the frontlines, it has been involved in cross-border raids into Russia, particularly in the Belgorod region, aiming to destabilize the Russian regime and encourage domestic resistance.

The group is a frequent target of Russian state propaganda, which labels its members as traitors and terrorists. However, the legion claims to fight for a democratic and free Russia, positioning itself as an armed resistance movement against Putin’s rule.

They are primarily manufactured by SEGA and distributed through resellers or as game prizes. They come in multiple sizes, from miniature sizes that can barely fit in the palm of your hand, all the way to Mega Jumbo size that are over a foot long and a headsize high. There have also been a few examples of Tera Jumbo Nesoberi for the Love Live cast, which can cover half of a whole bedlength.

A game based upon the Nesoberis was released for Japanese Exclusive mobile devices in 2018: [[Puchiguru Love Live!]], featuring only characters from μ's, Aqours, and Saint Snow. The game didn't last long and was shut down at the end of May in 2019.

title: flying_tigers
body:
The [b]American Volunteer Group[/b], better known as the "Flying Tigers", were three squadrons of American [[pilot]]s formed in 1941 to fly [[P-40 Warhawk]] fighters in the colors of the [[kuomintang|Republic of China]] against Japanese warplanes. Though the group was formed before America's official entry into [[World War II]] and intended to operate as mercenaries for the Chinese government outside of American authority, several delays meant that the AVG first flew in combat after the attack on [[Pearl Harbor]]. The fighter group gained legendary fame for providing positive headlines during a period when most news was bleak.

The AVG was disbanded just six months later, replaced by an official U.S. fighter group in the theater, though the new unit kept the "Flying Tigers" livery on many of their airplanes.

title: bokujou_monogatari

A multi-system farming simulation video game series. The player moves onto an abandoned or inherited farm and must rejuvenate their new hometown.

Most well-known in the West as [i]Harvest Moon[/i] (1997-2013), when it was distributed by Natsume. In 2014, Natsume lost the license to the series, and as the rights to the [[Harvest Moon (natsume)|]] name in the West is owned by them, the series renamed itself to [i]Story of Seasons[/i] outside of Japan.

The video game series [i][[Rune Factory]][/i] is a spin-off of the Bokujou Monogatari series; taking the game elements of Bokujou Monogatari and combining them with fantasy RPG game elements. Since 2019, the series also collaborated with [[Doraemon]] franchise and released two [i]Doraemon's Story of Seasons[/i] spin-off series.

title: sonic_channel
body:
The official Japanese-language website and online hub for the [i][[Sonic (series)|Sonic the Hedgehog]][/i] series, managed by [[Sega]] of Japan. Launched on November 21, 2003, it serves as an all-in-one resource for Sonic news, artwork, and fan engagement, with content often shared exclusively in Japanese before being referenced elsewhere.

[i]Sonic Channel[/i] regularly posts high-resolution illustrations and character art—sometimes featuring special events or anniversaries, as well as monthly calendar wallpapers that showcase unique poses or seasonal themes for Sonic and his friends. In addition to artwork, [i]Sonic Channel[/i] has hosted short web comics featuring various members of the [i]Sonic[/i] cast, often capturing lighthearted moments or side adventures.

Apply this tag to artwork that depicts characters wearing exclusive official alternate outfits, adopting distinct poses, or referencing specific themes/scenes that originated from the official [i]Sonic Channel[/i] monthly artwork, comics, or other unique site features (and remain exclusive to it).

The story follows [[Aki Tomoya]], a high school student who recruits his friends to help him create a visual novel based on his classmate, [[Katou Megumi]].

The series has received multiple adaptations: a manga series with art by [[Moriki Takeshi]] (and two further manga spinoff series), an anime series with two seasons by [[A-1 Pictures]], a [[Playstation Vita]] visual novel, and a movie by [[CloverWorks]] that premiered October 2019.

Common destroyer-class enemies, first introduced in the KanColle Operation Rei-Go 1944 stage play, and introduced into [[Kantai Collection]] proper during the Spring 2025 event. They are the only "normal enemy" aside from the imps with voice lines. Based on the art, they are assumed to be Abyssal forms of [[United States Navy]] destroyers, particularly of the [i]Allen M. Sumner[/i]-class.

Also unlike previous common enemies, the Ra-class has five separate forms: [[ra-class destroyer alpha|Alpha]], [[ra-class destroyer beta|Beta]], [[ra-class destroyer gamma|Gamma]], [[ra-class destroyer delta|Delta]], and [[ra-class destroyer zeta|Zeta]].

The following differences separate the forms:
* Alpha has [[long hair]], [[horns]] growing out of her hat, and a completely [[white necktie]].
* Beta has [[short hair]] that [[hair over one eye|completely covers her right eye]], [[spikes]] out of her hat, and a [[multicolored necktie]] that starts at white at the knot, and changes to red/yellow down her body. * Delta has [[twintails]] hair that [[hair over one eye|completely covers her left eye]], [[spikes]] out of her hat, and a completely [[red necktie]]. Unlike the other Ra-classes, Delta has [[multicolored gloves]] black and red [[elbow gloves]] that extend into the sleeves of her dress, and [[red straps]] atop her shoes.
* Zeta, in complete contrast to the others, has [[white hair]], a completely [[covered face]], a [[transparent necktie]], and [[garter straps]] connected to the horns out of her knees, with [[anchor]]s dangling from them. Each variation of this move differs depending on the character and game; for instance, Ryu's version will hit once with a strong kick, while Ken's hit's up to three times―depending on the button pressed. title: selena:_tempest_(pgr)
body:
The Uniframe of [[Selena (pgr)|]] from [[Punishing: Gray Raven]]. Namesake is the stage play written by William Shakespeare, The Tempest.

h4. Appearance
Selena has [[purple eyes]] and [[very long hair|very long]] [[straight hair|straight]] [[black hair]], has features like [[single sidelock]] (left side), [[blunt bangs]], [[colored inner hair]] ([[blue hair|blue]] or [[red hair|red]] inner), hair [[parted hair|parts]] into two at the lower back. Her hair is adorned with a single [[hair ribbon]] on the right side, wears a pair of [[earrings]].

The Tempest frame has many [[mechabare]] elements integrated into the body, she can be tagged as [[cyborg]] depending on the level of mechanical details depicted. Both arms are [[mechanical arms|mechanical]] as well as her left [[mechanical legs|leg]] ([[single mechanical leg]]), both feet are [[mechanical foot|mechanical]], but depending on depiction, right foot might look like a [[black footwear|black]] [[boots|boot]] ([[asymmetrical footwear]]). Has [[robot joints]] at her elbow, wrist, knee and ankle.

Her apparel is a [[black dress|black]] [[armored dress]], with [[puffy long sleeves]], a [[black bow|black]] [[waist bow]], and skirt with [[pleated skirt|pleated]] design. No other apparel on the lower body.

Depending on awakening level of the character depicted, her hair ribbon can be replaced by two [[hairclip]]s, and her skirt armor plates can be depicted [[glowing armor|glowing]]. She uses a weaponized [[cello]] in combat, but the acoustic chamber is missing entirely, and the endpin is a blade. Also carries the [[bow (music)|bow]] to play the cello.

title: garry's_mod
body:
Sandbox physics game created by Garry Newman and developed by Facepunch Studios on PC.

The game was originally a mod for [[valve_software|Valve Corporation]]'s [[Half-Life 2]] Death Match, but was made a standalone game in 2006 for Windows. An OS X version was released in 2010, and a Linux version was released in 2013.

The game has no set objective and instead gives the player the freedom to make his/her own maps, add ragdolls to the map, and manipulate the ragdolls.

Due to its freedom, players or developers are able to make custom game modes for Garry's Mod, such as "Trouble in Terrorist Town":[https://wiki.facepunch.com/gmod/gamemodes/Trouble_In_Terrorist_Town] and "Murder":[https://github.com/MechanicalMind/murder]. Content creators can also use its freedom to make videos through stop motion of ragdolls and props posing for frames and rendering them into a GMod video.

Garry's Mod runs on the [i]Source[/i] engine made by [[valve software|Valve]], along with other games like [[Team Fortress 2]] and Counter Strike: Source. As a result, many mods for Garry's Mod borrow assets from those games.

h4. See also

title: foreman_spike
body:
A character from [i][[Wrecking Crew]][/i]. Described as a "mean old man" (意地悪おじさん) in the original Japanese manual and as a "Foreman" in the original English manual. He attempts to impede the progress of [[Mario]] or [[Luigi]] by destroying any walls, ladders, or pillars they are near, forcing them to fall. Functionally he performs the same role as Luigi's CPU did in [i]Vs. Wrecking Crew[/i].

While most of his appearances have very different looks from each other, his most consistent traits are that he wears [[sunglasses]] and has a [[beard]], though in [i]Wrecking Crew '98[/i] he is clean shaven with a visible [[cleft chin]]. In [i]Mobile Golf[/i] he was given a more [[fat_man|rotund]] body similar to that of [[Wario]]. 

Was originally known as [b]Blackey/Blacky[/b] (ブラッキー), until his appearance in [[the Super Mario Bros. Movie]] led to him adopting his international name [b]Spike[/b] (スパイク) in Japan.

title: kaiboukan_no._30_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese escort ship [i]Number 30[/i]. Nicknamed Mito (みと). Character designed by [[Hozuka (kadokawa)|]]. 

She has [[short_hair|short]] [[grey hair]] tied into [[double_bun|small buns]] tied to ribbons with small anchors in the ends and [[grey eyes]]. Her default outfit is shared with her sisters: a [[white headwear|white]] [[sailor hat]], a [[white dress|white]] [[sailor dress]] with a [[blue_sailor_collar|blue]] [[sailor collar]], blue accents, [[yellow bow]] with a pair of [[uwabaki]], and [[black pantyhose]]. 

Her [[rigging]] basically consists of a miniature version of her namesake ship slung to her left like a bag, a 12 cm [[handgun]] mount, and several [[depth charge]]s, one around each thigh and several in a cage container wrapped in green cloth.

The historical [i]Number 30[/i] had an uneventful history with her only highlight being her survival from torpedo attacks twice. She was sunk by Royal Navy aircraft at Yura on July 28, 1945 and eventually salvaged and scrapped in 1948.

title: inomata_mutsumi
body: Female Illustrator most known for her anime character design work in the early to mid 1980s. That her designs defined the first half of that decade would be an understatement. She provided the character designs for [i]Leda: Fantastic Adventure of Yohko[/i] and [i]Windaria[/i]; and  for "Tales of" video game series. Worked with "Team Destiny" in the Namco Tales Studio. Inomata was also a prolific novel illustrator, known for her vivid watercolor paintings which often center around young women with wide, jewel-like eyes. "Passed away":[https://twitter.com/inomatanekomata/status/1769574473504883081] on March 10, 2024. Her family never disclosed the cause of her death.

title: rody_soul
body:
Rody Soul is a minor character from [[Boku No Hero Academia]].

h4. Appearance

Rody is a young man with spiky [[brown hair]] tied into a [[high ponytail|high]] [[split ponytail]], along with [[grey eyes]] and sun-kissed skin.

He wears a [[red bandana]] along with a pair of [[sunglasses]] [[eyewear on head|on his head]], as well as a pale [[blue shirt|blue button-up shirt]] with a number of [[patches|]] and a [[beige jacket|tan-beige jacket]] with an [[orange flower]] sticking out from the left chest pocket. He wears a pair of thick, [[grey gloves]] and a blue and red [[striped necktie|striped tie]]. He also wears a pair of [[black pants]] that stop just above his ankles with patches on the knees, as well as a pair of dark [[brown footwear|brown shoes]] with a gray cloth wrapped around each of them.

title: hype_beast_crypto
body:
A [[official alternate costume|legendary skin]] for [[Crypto (apex legends)|]] in [[Apex Legends]], inspired by [[streetwear]] and Korean [[hip hop]] [[fashion]]. The skin is permanently available and can be crafted for 1200 crafting materials. Infamous among fans, as it's bold and overt style clashes with Crypto's careful and secretive characterization.

In this appearance, Crypto has [[undercut]] [[blonde hair]] worn in tied [[cornrows]], a [[bandaid on stomach|bandaid on his stomach]], and wears  [[grey pants]], [[purple footwear|purple]] [[sneakers]], [[sunglasses]], a [[gold chain]] and an [[open jacket|open]] [[multicolored jacket]] exposing his [[bare pectorals]].

For Season 12's anniversary event, [[Mirage (apex legends)|]] and [[Wattson (apex legends)|]] recieved new legendary skins based on Hype Beast ([[Lit Witt Mirage|Lit Witt]] and [[Thunder Kitty Wattson|Thunder Kitty]] respectively). This in turn prompted a trend of artists drawing their own interpretations of Hype Beast-inspired skins for the rest of the legends.

title: vestia_zeta_(new_year)
body:
The 2nd/New Year [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive Indonesia|hololive ID]]'s [[Vestia Zeta]].

It consists of an [[off shoulder|off-shoulder]] [[short kimono|short]] [[black kimono]] with  [[long sleeves|long]] [[wide sleeves]]  and a [[pelvic curtain]], multiple [[thigh strap]]s, [[bandaged leg|bandages on her left leg]], [[white socks|white]] [[tabi]] and [[black footwear|black]] [[okobo]]. She also wears a [[single earring|single]] black [[tassel earrings|tassel earring]].

She has 2 different [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyles]] in this costume.
* [[Short hair]] with [[short hair with long locks|long]] [[sidelocks]]
* [[Long hair]] done in a [[two side up]].
Both hairstyles have [[double-parted bangs|double-parted]] [[center-flap bangs]] that are decorated with a [[black bow|black]] [[hair bow]] and [[hair flower]]s

h4. Appearance

* !asset #15444937: Profile

title: vestia_zeta_(jirai_kei)
body:
The 3rd [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive Indonesia|hololive ID]]'s [[Vestia Zeta]], as seen on "Twitter":[https://twitter.com/hololive_Id/status/1691465616337883139], it has a [[jirai kei]] theme.

It consists of a [[white shirt]] with [[long sleeves|long]] [[frilled sleeves]] and [[frilled shirt collar|collar]], a [[black choker|black]] [[studded choker]] with a [[pendant choker|pendant]] of traditional indonesian shadow puppets called [i]wayang[/i], a [[blue bowtie]], [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]], a pair of black [[suspenders]] holding a [[black skirt|black]] [[high-waist skirt|high-waist]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]] with a wayang [[print skirt|print]] a [[cat o-ring]] [[o-ring thigh strap|thigh_strap]] [[black socks|black]] [[loose socks]] and [[grey slippers|grey]] [[cat slippers]]. She also has a [[handgun]], a [[blue bag|blue]] [[handbag]] and [[cat ear headphones]] as optional accessories.

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this outfit is [[short hair]] in a [[bob cut]] with a [[side_braid|side]] [[ribbon braid]].

h4. Appearance

* !asset #15444932: Profile

title: hezi
body:
Hezi is a [[hanfu]] top that can be worn as outerwear or as an undergarment. Hezi is strapless, similar to a [[bandeau]] or a [[tube top]].

Hezi can be worn with various styles, mostly commonly [[qixiong ruqun]]. 

[[Heziqun]] is [b]always[/b] worn with a hezi, but not all clothes with a hezi is a heziqun.
